ground with you and her in it.

20:45.400 --> 20:47.675
You do as I say!

20:48.760 --> 20:51.115
D'you have any idea who I am?

20:51.200 --> 20:54.112
I know exactly who you are,
Mr Maguire.

20:55.760 --> 20:57.671
Stop. Don't go!

20:57.760 --> 21:01.070
(Shouts) Don't you walk away from me!

21:01.160 --> 21:02.639
Don't go!

21:02.720 --> 21:05.154
<i>Fu-u-u-u-ckl</i>

21:06.800 --> 21:09.837
Go on, it's all right. Don't be scared.

21:11.520 --> 21:14.557
- All right, Lillian?
- Looking for something special?

21:14.640 --> 21:16.995
Oh, it's not... All right, love?
No, it's not for me.

21:17.080 --> 21:19.640
It's for my compadre here. Yeah?

21:19.720 --> 21:24.157
- Hiya.
- What can I get for 30 quid?

21:24.240 --> 21:28.313
Thirty'll get you a Colombian Handshake
or a Paisley Snowjob.

21:28.400 --> 21:31.790
But for an extra tenner, I can chuck you
in a Yugoslavian Quarterpounder,

21:31.880 --> 21:33.552
which is popular with the young 'uns.

21:33.640 --> 21:37.030
Just, you know, a traditional
roll in the hay will be all right.

21:37.120 --> 21:39.873
- Go on, then, love.
- Go on, go on.

21:39.960 --> 21:43.270
- Come on, then.
- Everything is so lovely here.

21:43.360 --> 21:47.399
No rush, Bernard. You just
lose yourself up there, all right?

21:47.480 --> 21:51.234
We'll talk later.
All right, Leanne?

21:51.320 --> 21:53.754
- Fine, thanks.
- How's your gran?

21:53.840 --> 21:55.558
- She's all right.
- Great...

21:55.640 --> 21:57.631
LOUD VOMITING FROM UPSTAIRS

21:57.720 --> 21:58.914
Jesus!

21:59.000 --> 22:01.639
(Bernard) I'm so... I'm so sorry.

22:04.720 --> 22:07.393
Frank, I don't feel so good.

22:11.840 --> 22:14.434
I think we'd better
call it a night, then.

22:16.280 --> 22:18.111
I know there's someone there!

22:18.200 --> 22:21.670
Listen, I'm sorry.
Whatever it is you think I've...

22:21.760 --> 22:24.911
<i>Whatever it is I have done,
I'm sorry, OK?</i>

22:30.040 --> 22:32.235
Hello?!

22:33.320 --> 22:35.072
Please, I need...

22:43.160 --> 22:44.639
Fuck!

22:46.080 --> 22:47.274
KNOCK AT DOOR

22:57.040 --> 22:58.359
DOOR CLOSES

23:01.800 --> 23:05.475
Frank, what the hell's the benefits
officer doing in Debbie's bed?

23:05.560 --> 23:07.710
Ideally, waking up to a new life.

23:07.800 --> 23:10.155
One where the idea of helping out
his fellow man -

23:10.240 --> 23:12.993
ie, you and me, Monica -
is most appealing.

23:13.080 --> 23:14.672
What are you babbling on about?

23:16.440 --> 23:19.637
I tried to expand his horizons,
you know?

23:19.720 --> 23:24.271
Sort of, you know, slipped him
a couple of Es to change his world view -

23:24.360 --> 23:26.112
give him his own mini-Woodstock.

23:26.200 --> 23:29.909
You know, welcome to Spike Island,
leave yer preconceptions at the door.

23:30.000 --> 23:32.230
- And that worked, did it?
- Sort of.

23:35.080 --> 23:36.433
No, not really.

23:37.720 --> 23:38.948
Oh, all right! I fucked it.

23:40.400 --> 23:43.437
We're in the shit here, Monica.
It's not funny.

23:43.520 --> 23:47.513
It's not just cutting benefits off.
We're talking jail here.

23:47.600 --> 23:49.431
They don't send you to jail just for that!

23:49.520 --> 23:52.717
The place is teeming with 'em.
They don't fuck around.

23:52.800 --> 23:55.268
Come on, seriously.

23:55.360 --> 23:57.749
Strangeways, here we come. Again.

23:57.840 --> 23:59.876
No way. I can't do jail.

23:59.960 --> 24:02.030
I'm not wanting
to Steve McQueen it meself.

24:02.120 --> 24:04.270
Plus they're gonna take away the kids.

24:04.360 --> 24:07.796
You can wave goodbye to lickle Stella
up there, the house, everything.

24:07.880 --> 24:10.917
- Well, we've got to do something.
- All right.

24:12.400 --> 24:14.595
We've got the answer, though.

24:18.800 --> 24:23.351
Right here under our roof.
Lying there, in bed. Benefits Boy.

24:23.440 --> 24:26.432
Look, it's simple mathematics.

24:26.520 --> 24:29.193
He's lonely. His wife's left him.

24:29.280 --> 24:31.589
It was his fucking birthday.

24:33.120 --> 24:34.553
Well, he's vulnerable, in't he?

24:36.280 --> 24:42.435
We've just got to show him a bit of...
care and attention -

24:42.520 --> 24:43.748
bit of love -

24:43.840 --> 24:47.435
so that he bins our report
and we're back laughing again.

24:47.520 --> 24:50.910
- What you getting at?
- I'm just saying, you know...

24:52.520 --> 24:54.988
...we need to be creative.

24:55.080 --> 24:58.834
Maybe... you could do something.

25:00.960 --> 25:04.509
You know, be nice to him.
The old feminine wiles and that.

25:10.840 --> 25:12.273
Fine.

25:13.840 --> 25:15.751
Fucking fine.

25:21.080 --> 25:23.150
DOOR OPENS

25:24.680 --> 25:30.471
Good morning, Patrick. Sorry I wasn't
able to look in on you first thing.

25:30.560 --> 25:33.518
There was a bring-and-buy sale
at the church.

25:33.600 --> 25:36.353
Really, some of the junk
people drag there!

25:36.440 --> 25:39.557
SHE LAUGHS
How did you sleep?

25:39.640 --> 25:41.358
Why do you ask me that question?

25:41.440 --> 25:43.112
I don't understand.

25:43.200 --> 25:45.316
Like I've just popped round.

25:45.400 --> 25:48.836
Kettle's boiling.
Some fucking cucumber sandwiches

25:48.920 --> 25:52.469
daintily arranged on a plate.
You have me tied to a fucking bed.

25:52.560 --> 25:56.758
- Honestly... language!
- What is it you want from me?

25:58.120 --> 25:59.997
You tell me I've got to understand.

26:00.080 --> 26:05.313
I don't understand
what the hell it is you expect from me.

26:05.400 --> 26:08.517
You've soiled yourself,
haven't you, Patrick?

26:08.600 --> 26:11.512
Sorry. These things happen.

26:11.600 --> 26:13.158
No. No, they don't.

26:13.240 --> 26:16.676
Not unless some psycho bitch
has tied you to a fucking bed.

26:16.760 --> 26:17.988
They do happen!

26:19.600 --> 26:24.116
People found lying
in their own excrement, turned blue,

26:24.200 --> 26:27.033
<i>life thrown away - it happensl</i>

26:33.880 --> 26:35.154
I can make it easier.

26:36.800 --> 26:38.279
I could clean you up.

26:38.360 --> 26:42.239
And you must be thirsty by now -
really thirsty. Would you like a drink?

26:44.200 --> 26:46.839
If you don't answer me,
I can't get you one.

26:46.920 --> 26:49.434
A glass of water, Patrick?
Yes or no?

26:49.520 --> 26:50.669
(Yes.)

26:50.760 --> 26:52.432
Yes.

26:52.520 --> 26:55.830
Right, so you'll have to do something
for me, then, Patrick.

26:55.920 --> 26:57.672
Do you sing?

26:57.760 --> 26:58.875
What?

26:58.960 --> 27:03.351
I bet you do.
The Irish love singing, don't they?

27:03.440 --> 27:05.874
What beautiful voices.

27:05.960 --> 27:08.918
Or is that...
is that racist to assume that?

27:09.000 --> 27:11.150
How the fuck should I know?

27:11.240 --> 27:14.152
(Shouts) What did I say to you
about language?

27:17.160 --> 27:18.639
Sorry.

27:21.320 --> 27:22.355
I'm really sorry.

27:27.440 --> 27:31.479
I'm having a bad day.
It happens sometimes.

27:34.200 --> 27:38.955
Did you ever see the musical
Bugsy Malone?

27:39.040 --> 27:41.235
I saw the movie.

27:41.320 --> 27:42.753
Yeah, of course you did.

27:42.840 --> 27:48.710
Well, there's a song in it,
We Could Have Been Anything.

27:48.800 --> 27:50.552
I think it's... apt.

27:51.720 --> 27:55.838
Could you indulge me, Patrick?
Sing for me.

27:55.920 --> 27:57.751
I don't know the words.

27:57.840 --> 28:00.149
Of course you don't.
Hang on a minute...

28:05.040 --> 28:06.678
Ta-da!

28:09.560 --> 28:11.073
I can get you started.

28:15.000 --> 28:18.788
♪ We could have been anything

28:18.880 --> 28:25.638
♪ That we wanted to be

28:25.720 --> 28:28.154
♪ And it...

28:28.240 --> 28:30.595
♪ And... ♪

28:33.840 --> 28:38.470
All I'm asking you to do
is sing, Patrick.

28:38.560 --> 28:39.879
(Shouts) Sing!

28:41.120 --> 28:44.351
♪ We could have been anything

28:44.440 --> 28:50.231
♪ That we wanted to be...

28:53.360 --> 28:56.432
♪ And it's not too late to change

28:57.640 --> 28:59.073
♪ - I'd be...
- Delighted...

28:59.160 --> 29:01.958
- #... To give it some thought... #
- Can't hear you, Patrick!

29:03.840 --> 29:09.517
♪... Maybe you'll agree
that we really ought... ♪

29:09.600 --> 29:11.670
He was sniffing your knickers?!

29:11.760 --> 29:13.955
No, I never said
he was sniffing 'em.

29:14.040 --> 29:16.429
Yeah, only cos you disturbed him.

29:16.520 --> 29:18.397
I'd have him hauled up for that.

29:18.480 --> 29:22.439
But that's just me. Unless, y'know...
you still fancy him.

29:22.520 --> 29:24.431
Shut up!

29:27.640 --> 29:31.076
So... when were you going to tell us
you were getting a promotion?

29:31.160 --> 29:34.709
Didn't think that was
anyone's business but mine.

29:34.800 --> 29:36.074
How did you swing that?

29:37.280 --> 29:38.838
Hard work.

29:38.920 --> 29:41.036
- Dedication.
- Yeah, right(!)

29:41.120 --> 29:44.078
Think I want to spend the rest
of my career wasting away in this dump?

29:44.160 --> 29:49.109
I made a choice. Sometimes
a girl's gotta do what a girl's gotta do.

29:53.320 --> 29:56.756
Oh, before I forget,
Super wants to see you.

29:56.840 --> 30:00.355
What about?
Could you not have told me earlier?!

30:00.440 --> 30:02.874
Yes, Tom, I suppose I could.

30:02.960 --> 30:06.635
I suppose I could stick toothpaste
on your toothbrush every morning,

30:06.720 --> 30:09.280
and warm your slippers,
and wipe your smelly bum,

30:09.360 --> 30:11.430
and hold your hand
as you cross the road.

30:11.520 --> 30:13.795
But that's not my job.

30:14.960 --> 30:19.112
For too long
I've let you losers drag me down.

30:19.200 --> 30:22.112
So grow a brain
and work it out for yourself, eh?

30:29.520 --> 30:31.556
Right...

30:31.640 --> 30:32.993
See ya.

30:40.200 --> 30:41.349
KNOCKING

30:42.400 --> 30:45.278
I'll be out of your hair in a minute.
I'm really sorry.

30:45.360 --> 30:48.352
Don't worry about it.

30:56.280 --> 30:58.555
- Are you OK?
- No.

30:58.640 --> 31:00.790
I didn't mean to impose...

31:00.880 --> 31:03.713
It's nothing to do with you at all.

31:12.400 --> 31:16.109
It's OK. It's OK, don't worry.

31:22.080 --> 31:25.516
He's a fucking psycho. There's something
seriously wrong with him.

31:25.600 --> 31:27.352
Don't need to tell me. He's me brother.

31:27.440 --> 31:31.513
Mum'll go mental if you kick him
out the team. Not worth the hassle.

31:31.600 --> 31:33.989
There's a fella I know through work,
can barely walk,

31:34.080 --> 31:37.914
but he'd be up for a game. Stick Micky
on the subs bench and it's problem sorted.

31:42.560 --> 31:43.515
Yeah.

31:43.600 --> 31:45.431
- Problem sorted.
- Speaking of problems,

31:45.520 --> 31:47.590
- we've got one.
- What?

31:47.680 --> 31:50.194
We can either go
to that expensive French restaurant

31:50.280 --> 31:52.191
where they turn their noses up at us,

31:52.280 --> 31:54.510
or we can go to the expensive Italian one.

31:54.600 --> 31:57.068
Tell you what,
life's just full of problems!

32:13.760 --> 32:16.752
It's all right.
You can look if you want.

32:16.840 --> 32:17.795
Fuck off.

32:17.880 --> 32:19.598
- Don't bother me.
- Poof!

32:29.280 --> 32:31.111
I fucking knew it!

32:33.560 --> 32:34.549
Carl!

32:34.640 --> 32:37.279
- Stay away from me, you fuckin' psycho.
- Wait!

32:38.240 --> 32:40.515
For fuck's sake, Micky,
what have you done?

32:40.600 --> 32:42.352
What? It was an accident.

32:42.440 --> 32:44.874
You know. I slipped.

32:47.720 --> 32:51.474
Oh, yes, yes, oh, don't stop...

32:53.360 --> 32:54.554
You're beautiful.

32:54.640 --> 32:56.995
You don't have to say that.

32:57.080 --> 33:00.914
But you are. Sorry.

33:01.000 --> 33:02.638
Just...

33:02.720 --> 33:04.950
you are beautiful, you know.

33:09.480 --> 33:10.913
Oh...!

33:17.240 --> 33:19.708
I presume you know
what this is about.

33:19.800 --> 33:21.153
I do.

33:21.240 --> 33:22.753
There are certain things
we frown on here...

33:22.840 --> 33:27.709
Can I just explain? First of all,
it wasn't like I didn't know her.

33:27.800 --> 33:32.874
We used to go out. And OK,
I admit, you step back, you look at it,

33:32.960 --> 33:36.475
yes, she was 15 when I met her,
but I didn't do anything.

33:36.560 --> 33:38.152
And she'd testify to that.

33:38.240 --> 33:41.073
And yes, technically,
I let myself in to the house

33:41.160 --> 33:44.436
which, if you look at it in the wrong way,
you might see as breaking and entering,

33:44.520 --> 33:47.114
but I was just putting
the chocolate in the drawer.

33:47.200 --> 33:50.510
Then I thought, "No, drawer,
that's invasion of privacy,

33:50.600 --> 33:51.999
"I'll stick them on the bed."

33:54.480 --> 33:57.950
Then the pants got snagged and...

33:58.040 --> 33:59.234
voila.

33:59.320 --> 34:00.833
Pants?

34:00.920 --> 34:02.558
As in... underwear?

34:02.640 --> 34:04.232
Yeah.

34:04.320 --> 34:05.639
Of a 15-year-old girl?

34:05.720 --> 34:10.157
No. Debbie's 16 now.
Why would she say she's 15?

34:10.239 --> 34:13.596
I have no idea who she is
or what you're talking about.

34:13.679 --> 34:16.513
We are here to discuss
the circumstances

34:16.600 --> 34:19.956
which led to Stanley Waterman
having to take extended sick leave.

34:20.040 --> 34:22.998
We've received a report
about the incident

34:23.080 --> 34:26.389
which we feel lays the groundwork
for a disciplinary procedure.

34:26.480 --> 34:28.516
You've received a report?

34:29.760 --> 34:33.116
Sometimes a girl's gotta do
what a girl's gotta do.

34:33.199 --> 34:36.397
A blatant abuse of position
and waste of resources.

34:36.480 --> 34:39.391
But maybe you should start again.

34:39.480 --> 34:42.313
The other story sounds
far more interesting.

34:42.400 --> 34:44.594
So...

34:44.679 --> 34:47.034
there was a 15-year-old girl...

34:50.560 --> 34:52.197
Fucking hell.

34:56.960 --> 34:58.632
I'll, um... Goodbye, then.

34:58.720 --> 34:59.755
Wait, wait, wait!

35:01.480 --> 35:02.833
What happened?

35:02.920 --> 35:07.152
Our case is gonna disappear
down behind some filing cabinet.

35:07.240 --> 35:10.471
Really? Yeah! Fucking genius, Mon.

35:10.560 --> 35:12.755
Fucking genius.
How did you convince him?

35:12.840 --> 35:16.310
Don't think we need to go
into the gory details, do we?

35:16.400 --> 35:19.597
